      <notesStmt>
        <note>The Śivanāmakalpalatālavāla of Bhāskararāya, with an incomplete commentary, Sudhāpū [Sudhāpūra], by Veṅkaṭācalasūri [Veṅkaṭācalapaṇḍita]. Commentary present only on the last portion of the text (ff. 16r-end), subsequent to the exposition on the 108 names of Śiva.</note>
        <note>Title Śivanāmakalpalatālavāla from colophon of commentary (f. 19r). Colophon of text (f. 18v) supplies Śivanāmāṣṭaśata as the title. Title of commentary from Aufrecht's Catalogus Catalogorum (2.154) and the critical edition (Śivanāmakalpalatālavāla of Śrī Bhāskararāya ,H. V. Nagaraja Rao, ed., Oriental Research Institute Series, no. 146 [Mysore: Oriental Research Institute, 1985]). The title supplied in the ms. (f. 19r) is Sudhāpū.</note>
        <note>Text cataloged incorrectly by Poleman as Śivanāmakalpalatā.</note>
        <note>Written 7 lines per leaf.</note>
        <note>Good condition. Mistakes indicated by two horizontal lines above the syllable in question. Marginal corrections.</note>
        <note>Text begins: śrīgaṇeśāya namaḥ. mokṣasyaikanidānam avjanayanabrahme[n]dracandrādibhir devaiḥ prāṇapadīkṛtaṁ kalimalapradhvaṁsi dharmāṅkuraḥ bhāratyāpi sudurnirūpamahitrayyantare gopitaṁ vaktuṙmaṅgaladaṁ śiveti vimalaṁ nāmaiva nastārakaṁ (verse 1).</note>
        <note>Colophon of text (f. 18v): iti kāśinivāsisāgnicityakratukṛdbhāskararāyabhāratī januṣaḥsaphalatvasi[d]dhaye śivanāmāṣṭaśataṁ vyavarvarīt.</note>
        <note>Colophon of commentary (f. 19r): iti śrīveṅkaṭācalasūripraṇītaḥ śivanāmakalpalatālavālasudhāpūḥ samāptaḥ. śrīsāmbasadāśivārpaṇam astuḥ. yādṛśaṁ pustakaṁ dṛṣṭvạ̄ tādṛśaṁ likhitaṁ mayā. yadi śuddham aśuddhaṁ vā mama doṣo na vidyate.</note>
      </notesStmt>
